Photosynthesis TPC fitting

20220829

PR data from heatwave timepoint 1 corals

Import data

Photodata_May <- read.csv("data/May_Photo_extracted_rates.csv")
Photodata_Dec <- read.csv("data/Dec_Photo_extracted_rates.csv")
Photodata <- rbind(Photodata_May,Photodata_Dec)

TPC fitting Padifeld et al rTPC and nls.multstart: A new pipeline to fit thermal performance curves in r
https://besjournals.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1111/2041-210X.13585

Sharpe Schoolfield 1981 model Schoolfield, R. M., Sharpe, P. J. H., & Magnuson, C. E. (1981). Non-linear regression of biological temperature-dependent rate models based on absolute reaction-rate theory. Journal of theoretical biology, 88(4), 719-731. https://doi.org/10.1016/0022-5193(81)90246-0

#Photosynthesis
Photodata$temp <- as.numeric(Photodata$Temp.Cat)
Photodata$micromol.cm2.h <- replace(Photodata$micromol.cm2.h, Photodata$micromol.cm2.h<0,0)
Photodata$transformed.rate <- log10(Photodata$micromol.cm2.h+1)

# choose model
get_model_names()
##  [1] "beta_2012"             "boatman_2017"          "briere2_1999"         
##  [4] "delong_2017"           "flinn_1991"            "gaussian_1987"        
##  [7] "hinshelwood_1947"      "joehnk_2008"           "johnsonlewin_1946"    
## [10] "kamykowski_1985"       "lactin2_1995"          "lrf_1991"             
## [13] "modifiedgaussian_2006" "oneill_1972"           "pawar_2018"           
## [16] "quadratic_2008"        "ratkowsky_1983"        "rezende_2019"         
## [19] "sharpeschoolfull_1981" "sharpeschoolhigh_1981" "sharpeschoollow_1981" 
## [22] "spain_1982"            "thomas_2012"           "thomas_2017"          
## [25] "weibull_1995"
#sharpeschoolhigh_1981

# get start vals
start_vals <- get_start_vals(Photodata$temp,Photodata$transformed.rate, model_name = 'sharpeschoolhigh_1981')

# get limits
low_lims <- get_lower_lims(Photodata$temp,Photodata$transformed.rate, model_name = 'sharpeschoolhigh_1981')
upper_lims <- get_upper_lims(Photodata$temp,Photodata$transformed.rate, model_name = 'sharpeschoolhigh_1981')

#view values
start_vals
##     r_tref          e         eh         th 
##  0.1312832 -0.1584728  5.0000000 30.1208054
start_vals <- start_vals %>% replace(is.na(.), 0)
start_vals
##     r_tref          e         eh         th 
##  0.1312832 -0.1584728  5.0000000 30.1208054
low_lims
## r_tref      e     eh     th 
##      0      0      0      1
upper_lims

##  0.4623299 10.0000000 20.0000000 36.0000000

#GRANDIS May

# grandis CURVE FIT
# Haplotype_1a
d.grandis.may <- Photodata %>% 
  filter(mtORF=="Haplotype_1a")%>% 
filter(Season=="May")

#fit 
grandis.fit.may <- nls_multstart(transformed.rate~sharpeschoolhigh_1981(temp = temp, r_tref,e,eh,th, tref = 28),
                                                     data = d.grandis.may,
                                                     iter = 500,
                                                     start_lower = start_vals - 1,
                                                     start_upper = start_vals + 1,
                                                     lower = low_lims,
                                                     upper = upper_lims,
                                                     supp_errors = 'Y')

grandis.fit.may
## Nonlinear regression model
##   model: transformed.rate ~ sharpeschoolhigh_1981(temp = temp, r_tref,     e, eh, th, tref = 28)
##    data: data
##  r_tref       e      eh      th 
##  0.1671  0.0265 20.0000 32.7915 
##  residual sum-of-squares: 0.1249
## 
## Number of iterations to convergence: 19 
## Achieved convergence tolerance: 1.49e-08
#generate the predicted data
grandis_new_data.may <- data.frame(temp = seq(min(d.grandis.may$temp), max(d.grandis.may$temp), 0.5))
grandis.preds.may <- augment(grandis.fit.may, newdata = grandis_new_data.may)

#calculate TPC parameters
grandis.TCP.res.may <- calc_params(grandis.fit.may) %>%
  mutate_all(round, 2)   # round 

grandis.TCP.res.may 
##   rmax  topt ctmin ctmax    e    eh  q10 thermal_safety_margin
## 1 0.17 30.14  -Inf 33.99 0.03 10.14 1.03                  3.85
##   thermal_tolerance breadth skewness
## 1               Inf   10.25   -10.11
### Bootstrapping ambient curve fit    
# refit model using nlsLM
grandis.fit_nlsLM.may <- minpack.lm::nlsLM(transformed.rate~sharpeschoolhigh_1981(temp = temp, r_tref,e,eh,th, tref = 28),
                        data = d.grandis.may,
                        start = coef(grandis.fit.may),
                        lower = low_lims,
                        upper = upper_lims,
                        weights = rep(1, times = nrow(d.grandis.may)))

# bootstrap using case resampling
grandis.boot1.may <- Boot(grandis.fit_nlsLM.may, method = 'case')

# look at the data
head(grandis.boot1.may$t)
##         r_tref          e eh       th
## [1,] 0.1754083 0.15503929 20 33.54433
## [2,] 0.1579657 0.08366657 20 32.61566
## [3,] 0.1720972 0.00000000 20 32.84147
## [4,] 0.1575732 0.09046195 20 34.15650
## [5,] 0.1679398 0.36011670 20 32.47847
## [6,] 0.1783610 0.04822926 20 34.32094
# create predictions of each bootstrapped model
grandis.boot1_preds.may <- grandis.boot1.may$t %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  drop_na() %>%
  mutate(iter = 1:n()) %>%
  group_by_all() %>%
  do(data.frame(temp = seq(min(d.grandis.may$temp), max(d.grandis.may$temp), length.out = 100))) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(pred = sharpeschoolhigh_1981(temp, r_tref, e, eh, th, tref = 28))

# calculate bootstrapped confidence intervals
grandis.boot1_conf_preds.may <- group_by(grandis.boot1_preds.may, temp) %>%
  summarise(conf_lower = quantile(pred, 0.025),
            conf_upper = quantile(pred, 0.975)) %>%
  ungroup()

# plot bootstrapped CIs
grandis.CI.plot.May <- ggplot() +
  geom_line(aes(temp, .fitted), grandis.preds.may, col = 'orange') +
  geom_ribbon(aes(temp, ymin = conf_lower, ymax = conf_upper), grandis.boot1_conf_preds.may, fill = 'orange', alpha = 0.3) +
  geom_point(aes(temp, transformed.rate), d.grandis.may, size = 2, alpha = 0.5,col = 'orange') +
  theme_bw(base_size = 12) +
  labs(x = 'Temperature (C)',
       y = 'Log 10 +1 Rate (mol O2/cm2/h)')
grandis.CI.plot.May

 #set plot colors

# plot data and model fit
TPC.plot <- ggplot(data=Photodata, aes(x=temp)) +
   geom_point(aes(temp, transformed.rate, color="grandis.May"), d.grandis.may, size = 2, alpha = 0.5) +
   geom_point(aes(temp, transformed.rate, color="grandis.Dec"), d.grandis.dec, size = 2, alpha = 0.5) +
   geom_point(aes(temp, transformed.rate, color="verrucosa.May"), d.verrucosa.may, size = 2, alpha = 0.5) +
   geom_point(aes(temp, transformed.rate, color="verrucosa.Dec"), d.verrucosa.dec, size = 2, alpha = 0.5) +
   geom_line(aes(temp, .fitted), grandis.preds.may, col = 'orange', size=2) +
   geom_line(aes(temp, .fitted), grandis.preds.dec, col = 'brown', size=2) +
   geom_line(aes(temp, .fitted), verrucosa.preds.may, col = "cyan", size=2) +
   geom_line(aes(temp, .fitted), verrucosa.preds.dec, col = "blue", size=2) +
   geom_ribbon(aes(temp, ymin = conf_lower, ymax = conf_upper), grandis.boot1_conf_preds.may, fill = "orange", alpha = 0.3) +
  geom_ribbon(aes(temp, ymin = conf_lower, ymax = conf_upper), grandis.boot1_conf_preds.dec, fill = "brown", alpha = 0.3) +

  geom_ribbon(aes(temp, ymin = conf_lower, ymax = conf_upper), verrucosa.boot1_conf_preds.may, fill = 'cyan', alpha = 0.3) +
  geom_ribbon(aes(temp, ymin = conf_lower, ymax = conf_upper), verrucosa.boot1_conf_preds.dec, fill = 'blue', alpha = 0.3) +
   xlim(21,37)+
  ylim(0,0.45)+
   scale_x_continuous(breaks=c(22,24,26,28,30,32,34,36))+
   theme_bw(base_size = 12) +
   scale_colour_manual(name="Morphology",values=cols)+
   theme(legend.position = "none",
         panel.border = element_blank(), panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
         panel.grid.minor = element_blank(), axis.line = element_line(colour = "black"))+
   labs(x = 'Temperature (C)',
        y = expression("Log 10 +1 Rate"~mol~O[2] ~cm^{-2}~h^{-1}))

#GRANDIS May

#calculate all the TPC parameters
grandis.extra_params.may <- calc_params(grandis.fit_nlsLM.may) %>%
  pivot_longer(everything(), names_to =  'param', values_to = 'estimate')

#calculate CIs for all the TPC parameters
grandis.ci_extra_params.may <- Boot(grandis.fit_nlsLM.may, f = function(x){unlist(calc_params(x))}, labels = names(calc_params(grandis.fit_nlsLM.may)), R = 200, method = 'case') %>%
  confint(., method = 'perc') %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  rename(conf_lower = 1, conf_upper = 2) %>%
  rownames_to_column(., var = 'param') %>%
  mutate(method = 'case bootstrap')
## 
##  Number of bootstraps was 85 out of 200 attempted
#join the parameters and CIs  
grandis.ci_extra_params.may <- left_join(grandis.ci_extra_params.may, grandis.extra_params.may)
grandis.ci_extra_params.may$Treatment <- "Haplotype_1a May"
